If postal orders do not exist in your
country, or for any other problem,
don't hesitate to contact us.






»CL8:            Competitions:
»CL9:-------------------------------------

»CL1:AMIGA COMPETITIONS:

»CL0:Productions must have the possibility
to be quit by a mouse click.

»CL1:Configuration:»

A1200 with 060/66, 32MB, or 040/25 +
PPC603/200, 64MB under shell with
setpatch.

»CL1:Demo:»
Size of the demo: 4MB max.
No pure animation.
Maximum running length: 10 minutes.


»CL1:Intro:»
Size of the intro: 64KB max.
Maximum running length: 5 minutes.

»CL1:4K Intro:»
Size of the intro: 4096 bytes max.
Sound ALLOWED.
Maximum running length: 5 minutes.

(»CL8:PC Demos Cut -CTN»)

        »CL9:----»CL8:  WATCH OUT!»CL9:  ----

»CL0:All executable Productions must leave
properly to the system.

»CL9:ANY PRODUCTION NOT RESPECTING THIS
RULE WILL BE DISCARDED.


»CL1:GFX COMPETITIONS:

»CL0:Productions will be shown using SEA
(on PC).

»CL1:2D drawing:» no scan.

Rendered images.

»CL1:ANIMATION COMPETITION:»
Any type of animation, no exotic
format (or provide the player).

»CL1:MUSIC COMPETITIONS:»

Maximum listening time: 7'30".
4-voice module: played under
Deli-Tracker.
Maximum size: the one of an Amiga
disk (880KB).
Multi-voice module: played under
Cubic with an AWE32 8MB (or GRAVIS on
request).
Maximum size: the one of an HD PC
disk (1.44MB).

»CL1:WILD COMPO:»

Any medium (VHS, Animation, woman,
etc...).
Any delirium (etc...).
Maximum time: 10 minutes or maybe
more!

    »CL9:    ----»CL8:  WATCH OUT!»CL9:  ----

»CL0:Some competitions may be grouped by
category according to the number of
competitors.

Votes will determine 3 winners by
category. These will receive prizes
in cash and/or hardware, in
proportion to the number of people
present.

